    "note": "At the Q90 crossing the ridge runs at clipped mid-ladder load (rho_ach median ~3.8), so the detected-rate ratio there (median 16.27) is ~0.81x the terminal 20.1. The residual factor (median 1.25, ridge reaches Q90 with ~25% fewer detected photons) nearly cancels this, leaving NORMAL-scene median S=20.38 (slightly ABOVE 20.1). Thus the clip does NOT explain a net shortfall on NORMAL scenes; it is offset by per-photon efficiency. The 20.1->19.13 net move is the censoring of 3 hard scenes. Per-scene identity S=rate_ratio*residual is exact (see check_product)."
  },
